<plot>Between 1994 and 1999, 18 Plano youths died of a heroin overdose. In 1997, city officials went to the media about the situation and dubbed Plano, "Heroin-City, USA." A slew of teenage wasteland stories followed bringing national attention to Plano. This film is a study of how a suburban community came into existence and was then faced with an unignorable social problem, evaluated, interpreted, and sought to solve it.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?434785</url></doc>
